<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12092g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12092g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12092g"> 92(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> chiliarch</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The priests insisted on Mary&apos;s banishment by the governor. He sent a <mark>chiliarch</mark> to Bethlehem with thirty men. The Spirit told the apostles to take Mary to Jerusalem. They did so and held a five days&rsquo; service. Meanwhile the chiliarch found nothing at Bethlehem, and the priests said this was due to magic. <small> Montague Rhodes James, <a name="APNT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#APNT"><cite title="source">The Apocryphal New Testament</cite></a> (1924) 220</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Chiliarch: commander of a thousand men. </mm> </dd></dl>
